xts for image repair are examined: corporate, political, sports/entertainment, international, and third party (when one person or organization tries to repair the image of another). The book’s case studies include current instances of reputation repair, including Vladimir Putin on Ukraine and President Joe Biden on Afghanistan; Southwest Airlines on flight cancellations; Kobe Bryant on accusations of rape; and Donald Trump on the January 6 hearings.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCommunication. 0aDiscourse analysis. 0aRhetorical criticism. 0aVerbal self-defense. 4aBusiness and Economics : Business Communication. 4aCommunication : Communications. 4aTextbooks and Course Materials (Interdisciplinary) : Communications - Textbook. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Communication Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2024z978311149259940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849608540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438496085423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438496085/original  a978-3-11-149259-9  SUNY Press eBook Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles